data.name: Savory Beef Tacos with Avocado Crema
data.quickTastyDescription: Flavorful beef tacos topped with creamy avocado and fresh salsa, perfect for a lively dinner!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown the ground beef until fully cooked, about 8-10 minutes. Drain excess fat if necessary.
Add taco seasoning to the beef along with 1/2 cup of water. Stir well to combine and simmer for 5 minutes until thickened.
While the beef is simmering, prepare the avocado crema by blending the avocado, Greek yogurt, lime juice, and cilantro until smooth. Season with salt to taste.
Warm the corn tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave until pliable.

To assemble the tacos, place a generous amount of seasoned beef on each tortilla, then top with chopped lettuce, diced cherry tomatoes, sliced green onions, shredded cheese, and a drizzle of avocado crema.
Serve immediately and enjoy your flavorful tacos!
